{"description":"When checking accessiblity of a symbol found during resolution, it should be checked from the call site and not from the owner type. \r\n\r\ncurrently, such cases won\u0027t resolve methods properly : \r\n\r\n{code}\r\npackage p1;\r\npublic class A extends B {}\r\nclass B {\r\npublic int foo(){};\r\n}\r\n\r\npackage p2;\r\nclass C  {\r\n  void fun(A a) {\r\n     a.foo(); // Method not resolved if accessibility checked from owner as classes are not in the same package\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"3.6"}